body:
Sorry for lateness. I am working on this. The `offset:null` part can be removed from codes. However,  I noticed that there will be NO offset with 0 returned from response.

```
curl -X GET 'localhost:15984/db01/_all_docs?include_docs=true&keys=["point2"]&update_seq=true' -u foo:bar -g|jq .
 
{
  "total_rows": 5,
  "update_seq": null,
  "rows": [
    {
      "id": "point2",
      "key": "point2",
      "value": {
        "rev": "1-d942f0ce01647aa0f46518b213b5628e"
      },
      "doc": {
        "_id": "point2",
        "_rev": "1-d942f0ce01647aa0f46518b213b5628e",
        "type": "Feature",
        "geometry": {
          "type": "Point",
          "coordinates": [
            0.2,
            0.2
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

The same for POST method:
```
curl -u foo:bar -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" http://127.0.0.1:15984/db01/_all_docs --data "{\"include_docs\":\"true\",\"keys\":[\"point2\"]}"|jq .
{
  "total_rows": 5,
  "rows": [
    {
      "id": "point2",
      "key": "point2",
      "value": {
        "rev": "1-d942f0ce01647aa0f46518b213b5628e"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

I will proceed to issue PR if there is objection.

